Melt the butter in a medium saucepan. Add the onion and leek and cook until softened - about 10-15 minutes on a low heat.Add a splash of white wine, the potatoes, stock and seasoning and simmer until the potatoes are tender.Liquidise using a hand-held blender, or transfer to a liquidiser. Pass through a sieve before adding the milk and cream.Chill in the fridge until ready to serve.Sprinkle with chives and parsley just before serving.